results.name: Number of directed Hamiltonian paths in the n X n knight graph.
comment: Previous name was: Number of knight's paths visiting each square of an n X n chessboard exactly once.
link: P. Hingston, G. Kendall, Enumerating knight's tours using an ant colony algorithm, The 2005 IEEE Congress on Evolutionary Computation, 2 (2006), 1003-1010
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Hamiltonian Path
Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Knight Graph
example: For n=5 the numbers in the table below give the number of knight's paths starting at the respective position on the 5 X 5 chessboard.  In total there are a(5) = 304*4 + 56*8 + 64 = 1728 solutions.
xref: Cf. Undirected Hamiltonian paths: A169696 (3 X n), A079137 (4 X n), A083386 (5 X n), A306281 (6 X n), A306283 (7 X n), A308131 (n X n).
